lead_paragraph: Perry Ellis had 27 points and 13 rebounds, Devonte Graham hit a go-ahead free throw in the third overtime, and No. 1 Kansas won an early showdown of Final Four contenders.

headline.print_headline: In 3 Overtimes, No. 1 Kansas Ekes Past No. 2 Oklahoma
headline.main: In 3 Overtimes, No. 1 Kansas Ekes Past No. 2 Oklahoma

snippet: Perry Ellis had 27 points and 13 rebounds, Devonte Graham hit a go-ahead free throw in the third overtime, and No. 1 Kansas won an early showdown of Final Four contenders.
abstract: Top ranked Kansas defeats No 2 Oklahoma, 109-106, in third overtime.
